{"color":"TEAL","isTrashed":false,"isPinned":false,"isArchived":false,"textContent":"HOW TO SOLVE FOR CPI:\nAng basehang taon po natin sa CPI ay LAGING Total Weighted Price ng taong 2008 which is 1,300.\nCPI= Total Weighted Price ng kasalukuyang taon ÷ Total Weighted Price ng Basehang taon X 100.\nBale, kung kukuhanin mo ang CPI ng 2009:\n1,500÷1,300 X 100 = 115.38\nHOW TO SOLVE FOR INFLATION RATE/ ANTAS NG IMPLASYON:\nAntas ng Implasyon = CPI present yr minus CPI last year divided by CPI last year X 100.\nKukunin mo muna ang CPI ng 2010. Halimbawa, HALIMBAWA LANG PO ITO.\nHalimbawa, ang CPI ng 2010 ay 127.70, pag kukunin na ang Inflation rate, magiging ganito siya.\n127.70 minus 115.38 divided by 115.38 X 100 = 10.43%\nKaya po 115.38, kasi yun yung CPI ng previous year which is 2009. Ibig sabihin. Lahat nakabatay sa computation mo sa CPI.\nHOW TO SOLVE FOR PURCHASING POWER.\nPurchasing Power = 100 (CONSTANT) divided by CPI present year X 100.\nHalimbawa, pag kukunin ang Purchasing Power ng 2010, magiging ganito siya:\n100÷127.70 X 100= 79.43","title":"Ap","userEditedTimestampUsec":1483251314418000,"createdTimestampUsec":1483251304420000,"textContentHtml":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">HOW TO SOLVE FOR CPI:<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Ang basehang taon po natin sa CPI ay LAGING Total Weighted Price ng taong 2008 which is 1,300.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">CPI= Total Weighted Price ng kasalukuyang taon ÷ Total Weighted Price ng Basehang taon X 100.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Bale, kung kukuhanin mo ang CPI ng 2009:<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">1,500÷1,300 X 100 = 115.38<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">HOW TO SOLVE FOR INFLATION RATE/ ANTAS NG IMPLASYON:<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Antas ng Implasyon = CPI present yr minus CPI last year divided by CPI last year X 100.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Kukunin mo muna ang CPI ng 2010. Halimbawa, HALIMBAWA LANG PO ITO.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Halimbawa, ang CPI ng 2010 ay 127.70, pag kukunin na ang Inflation rate, magiging ganito siya.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">127.70 minus 115.38 divided by 115.38 X 100 = 10.43%<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Kaya po 115.38, kasi yun yung CPI ng previous year which is 2009. Ibig sabihin. Lahat nakabatay sa computation mo sa CPI.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">HOW TO SOLVE FOR PURCHASING POWER.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Purchasing Power = 100 (CONSTANT) divided by CPI present year X 100.<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Halimbawa, pag kukunin ang Purchasing Power ng 2010, magiging ganito siya:<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">100÷127.70 X 100= 79.43<\/span><\/p>","labels":[{"name":"Tareas"}]}